description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Senior Audiologist to join the Audiology team at North West Anglia NHS Foundation Trust. Based at Peterborough City Hospital, the role will primarily be focused upon the delivery of paediatric audiology services, but participation in the adult hearing aid service and diagnostic support to ENT clinics will be required. The post will include duties at the Trusts other hospital sites/clinic locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be qualified Audiologists with a BSc in Audiology or equivalent Audiology qualification and should meet the requirements for RCCP or HCPC registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicant should have a minimum of 2 years post qualification clinical experience in an NHS setting and have recent significant experience in the assessment and ongoing audiological management of young children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is looking for a highly motivated and flexible individual to join their friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameNathan StuartJob titleHead of AudiologyEmail addressnathan.stuart@nhs.netTelephone number 01733 677022&lt;/p&gt;
